<HEAD>Slots Banned In Laundries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Slot machines line the walls of
supermarkets and bars in this gaming resort, but they don't belong
in doughnut shops or laundries, officials decided.
   Clark County Commissioners voted Monday to prohibit new slot
machine licenses for machines in laundries, bakeries, doughnut
shops, fast-food restaurants, movie theaters and professional
offices.
   Existing licenses are not affected.
   Several owners of self-service laundries said they depend on
slot machine revenue to cover the high cost of doing business, with
the slots generating about 25 percent of revenues. Other laundry
owners stressed that customers need something to do to keep
occupied while their clothes spin and tumble.
   Commissioners said it is too hard to regulate the machines if
they are allowed to continue to proliferate in different businesses.
</TEXT>
