<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Mecham-Coverage     03-01 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Mecham-Coverage,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Statewide Audiences Have Radio, TV Coverage Available</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Mecham-Impeachment, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Public television stations are offering
gavel-to-gavel coverage of Gov. Evan Mecham's impeachment trial,
and several radio stations are covering portions of the proceedings.
   Public stations KUAT-TV in Tucson and KAET-TV in Phoenix started
providing full live coverage when the trial began Monday.
   KFYI, a Phoenix news and talk radio station, put together a
telephone network to feed continuous live coverage to stations in
Tucson, Flagstaff, Yuma, Bullhead City, Lake Havasu City, Sierra
Vista, Prescott Valley, Window Rock and Payson. Some of the
stations were carrying only part of the proceedings, however.
   None of Arizona's commercial television stations carried
gavel-to-gavel coverage, but many chipped in to set up pool
coverage with the public stations, in which all participants are
entitled to broadcast parts of the live proceedings or use excerpts
on later news programs.
   The pool costs could exceed $100,000, said Jim Willi of KPNX-TV
in Phoenix.
</TEXT>
