<HEAD>London Stocks Up In Early Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The London Stock Exchange posted gains in early
trading today, in line with rises in New York and Tokyo.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 13.3
points, or 0.75 percent, at 1782.1 by midmorning. The index opened
at 1781.1, up 12.2 points from Monday's close.
   Brokers said prices increased across the board before the
official opening, but profit-takers emerged to erase some gains.
   In contrast to the general rise, shares for retail stores were
largely unchanged because of growing caution about the prospect for
major tax cuts in the government's March 15 budget statement.
   The early trend followed sharp gains in New York on Monday,
where the Dow Jones industrial average rose 48.41 to 2,071.41, and
a rise overnight in Tokyo, where the Nikkei index climbed 193.09 to
25,435.90.
  
