<HEAD>Demonstrators Said to Mock Security Police</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities in southwestern Poland
detained 20 people for a march in which demonstrators wore hats,
black raincoats and dark glasses to mock secret security police, an
opposition activist said.
   The event in downtown Wroclaw was staged by the opposition group
Orange Alternative, which often uses satire to poke fun at Poland's
communist government.
   Spokesman Jozef Pinior said young men dressed in traditional spy
garb and sporting arm bands with the letters ``SB,'' the Polish
initials for Security Service, evoked laughter from onlookers.
   After about a half-hour, they were intercepted by real police
and 20 were taken into custody, he said. Authorities began
releasing them shortly afterward, he said.
   In the past, Orange Alternative demonstrators have donned Santa
Claus outfits and costumes of Lenten penitents to mock the
government's economic policies.
