<HEAD>Candidate Wins `Capital Case'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ed ReBrook, a candidate for the state
House and the Democratic National Convention, has won a ``capital
case.''
   ReBrook has been trying to persuade Secretary of State Ken
Hechler to list his name as ReBrook, not Rebrook, on the May 10
primary election ballot.
   Hechler argued the candidate has always signed his name Rebrook
and the bid for the capital letter was just a play for publicity
and an effort to make his name stand out on a crowded ballot.
   Kanawha County Circuit Judge Patrick Casey on Monday sided with
ReBrook, ruling that state election rules don't cover name
spelling, so Hechler ``is without constitutional or statutory
authority to determine the proper spelling or capitalization of (a
candidate's) name.''
   Hechler had no immediate comment.
