<HEAD>Sodium Cyanide Spilled on I-80</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARSON CITY, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sodium cyanide pellets were spilled on
a snowy section of Interstate 80 because of a truck wreck, and
nearly 100 miles of the highway was shut down as a small amount of
deadly cyanide gas formed.
   A nearby rail line crossing the unpopulated area was also closed
for a time.
   State Motor Vehicles Director Wayne Teglia said a
tractor-trailer rig overturned seven miles east of Battle Mountain,
injuring the driver and spilling about 100 pounds of pellets.
   Some gas formed when the pellets, used in mining operations,
reacted with the wet snow, Teglia said.
   ``If it had been raining it would have been worse,'' said Teglia.
   He said clean-up crews from the trucking company, Wells Cargo,
and a mining company were dispatched to clean up the spill.
