<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sumter Fire,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mobile Homes Burn On Sumter Lot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUMTER, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire spread through a mobile home sales
lot Tuesday, destroying 45 homes, authorities said.
   High wind and a lack of water hindered firefighters at Connor
Mobile Homes. There were no injuries reported in the Tuesday
morning fire.
   The mobile homes were valued about about $10,000 each. About
half the homes in the lot were destroyed.
   ``With the way the wind was blowing and just the three of us out
here, there was nothing we could do. It got up under the houses and
that was it,'' said Tony Cantrell, a Connor salesman.
   Fire Department Captain Richard Newman said the department
received a report of a grass fire and that the trailers were
burning when firefighters arrived.
