<1ST_LINE>r i BC-Lebanon-KidnapText     03-01 0406</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Lebanon-Kidnap Text,0412</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Text of New Statement on Higgins</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of a statement released
Tuesday, purporting to be from the kidnappers of kidnapped Lt. Col.
William R. Higgins, as translated from the Arabic by The Associated
Press:
   In the name of God, supporter of the oppressed, to the sons of
our struggling people in Lebanon and Palestine, to the free men of
the oppressed world.
   In addition to our previous statements on the detention of
American CIA agent Col. Higgins, we are keen to explain the
following:
   1. The propaganda that is being waged nowadays is aimed at
minimizing the espionage role of Col. Higgins and diverting the
issue of his detention into other incorrect objectives. It is also
aimed at circumventing his political activity with certain
suspicious currents and elements in the south.
   2. The attempts undertaken by the American administration and
the criminal Reagan (who) is moving inside and outside Lebanon to
ensure a quick release of Higgins so that he will not reveal
secrets and make confessions are aimed at stopping the
investigation of this criminal at a stage that will not allow us to
find out all about the American-Israeli conspiracies against our
people and nation. This is a failed attempt to wriggle out of the
impasse the Reagan administration is currently trapped in.
   3. But we declare today that we have uncovered solid facts about
an American-Israeli deal being hatched for south Lebanon. Once the
investigation of Higgins is over, we will place the details at the
disposal of our ulema (Moslem clergy) to make of them whatever they
deem fit.
   4. We reiterate that we shall continue the investigation of this
spy to complete his record, which is full of crimes. We shall put
forward all the facts to our people at the proper time.
   5. Israel's persistence in daily attacks to suppress the Islamic
uprising of the struggling Palestinian people and the steadfast
villages of Jebel Amel (Shiite name for south Lebanon), and the
shuttles of American criminal Shultz to abort the achievements of
this uprising will make us more determined to put this criminal
Higgins on trial. This will be done after the completion of the
investigation to make the world understand that any hand that
reaches out to hurt (our) pride, Islam and the dignity of our
people will be chopped off.
   The Organization of the Oppressed on Earth.
</TEXT>
