<DATELINE>MONTPELIER, Vt. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush, extending his
New England winning streak, defeated Sen. Bob Dole Tuesday in the
Vermont Republican presidential primary. The election was a
``beauty contest,'' with no national delegates at stake.
   Pat Robertson and Rep. Jack Kemp put up little effort and lagged
far behind the GOP front-runners.
