<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Southland Corp. is selling 473 7-Eleven stores in
10 states to its chief competitor, Circle K Corp., for more than
$147 million.
   The sale announced Monday would reduce Southland's 7-Eleven
chain to 7,542 from 8,296 stores before the company began
divestiture moves started last year.
   Company spokeswoman Markeeta McNatt said Southland plans to sell
hundreds more stores, lowering its total to between 7,000 and 7,300
by the end of 1989, to help reduce debt incurred in its $4.9
billion leveraged buyout.
