   The boards of directors at holding companies for
Dr Pepper and Seven-Up have agreed tentatively to merge the
privately-held soft-drink companies. Terms were not disclosed.
   The two companies, which accounted for nearly 11 percent of
sales in the $38 billion soft drink industry last year, said Monday
the proposed merger is contingent on drafting a definitive
agreement and regulatory approval.
