<HEAD>Peugeot Offers Trade-In Bonus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LYNDHURST, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peugeot Motors of America Inc. said it
was offering a $3,000 allowance to drivers who trade in their
Peugeots for the purchase or lease of a new Peugeot 505.
   ``The dollar's declining value has resulted in higher costs for
imported cars,'' said Pascal H. Henault, Peugeot's U.S. president.
   ``Since the resale value of used cars has not kept pace with new
car prices, we're compensating by offering a $3,000 trade-in
allowance.''
   To qualify, customers must prove they have owned or leased a
Peugeot for at least four months and the new car must be delivered
by May 31, the company said Monday in a statement.
