were killed in the attack by machine-gun and rocket fire.
   Pinochet on Tuesday credited providence with foiling the
reported plot in La Serena.
   ``God doesn't want to carry me off, so he helps me,'' Pinochet
told reporters in the southern city of Puerto Montt, where he was
inspecting public works projects. His remarks were broadcast by
Santiago radio stations.
   ``It give me more enthusiasm to fight for my country, as I am
doing,'' he said. ``I'm a lot luckier than they (extremists)
think.''
   He said it was only ``by chance'' that he did not travel to La
Serena as planned. ``There were a series of problems that obliged
me to stay in Santiago,'' he said without elaboration.
