<HEAD>Affiliated Publications Buy Interest In Xyquest Software Firm</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS style to delete commas before Inc. throughout,
CORRECTS Globe Newspaper from owner to publisher of Globe in last
graf.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Affiliated Publications Inc., owner of the Boston
Globe, said Tuesday it has bought a 40 percent equity interest in
Xyquest Inc. of Billerica, a developer of software for word
processing and publishing systems.
   Under the agreement, Affiliated will pay $3 million for newly
issued Xyquest shares.
   Xyquest, founded six years ago, developed the XyWrite word
processing line.
   In prepared remarks, Affiliated President John P. Giuggio said
of the investment, ``This is an exciting young company with a
promising future in electronic publishing. Xyquest has an excellent
management team, and we're delighted to be associated with it.''
   Xyquest President John Hild said the company's long-term goals
for product development include creating a full range of tools for
writing and editing and continuing to expand into corporate word
processing.
   Affiliated is parent company of Globe Newspaper Co., which
publishes the Globe. It also owns Billboard Publications Inc., The
Globe Pequot Press Inc., and a major interest in McCaw Cellular
Communications Inc.
